 Buckminster Fuller, Hollein, Friedman, u.a. sind die Protagonisten des architektonischen Schaffens im 20. Jahrhundert vertreten.50 Jahre nach Erscheinen ist mit dieser Sammlung von Quellentexten auch ein historisches Dokument der (Selbst-)Reflexion der Architektur wieder lieferbar.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aArchitekturgeschichte und -theorie. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / General.2bisacsh1 aArbeitsrat für Kunst,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehne,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuckminster Fuller, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiam,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConrads, Ulrich, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aConstant,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConstant/,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe 8,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Stijl,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDebord,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoesburg, Theo van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEesteren, van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFillon, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinsterlin, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedman, Yona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGabo, Naum, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeam,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGieselmann, Reinhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc